Higher half kernel is mapped into -2GB..0GB of virtual address space.
    -2GB..-1GB (0xffffffff80000000)is used for kernel static memory filled by bootloader. It is identity mapped to physical 0GB..1GB
    -1GB..0GB (0xffffffffc0000000) is used for kernel dynamic memory. It is dynamically mapped by PageFaultHandler
User memory is mapped into 0GB..1GB of virtual address space. It is dynamically mapped by PageFaultHandler